<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Middlesbrough advanced to the second round of the Carabao Cup after a thrilling 4-3 victory over League One side Shrewsbury.</p>

<p>Scott High put the visitors ahead before Marvin Johnson and a brace from Ashley Fletcher put Neil Warnock's side 3-1 up.</p>

<p>Jason Cummings for Shrewsbury to make it 3-2 before Marcus Tavernier added a fourth and Middlesbrough were able to hold on for a victory despite Rekeil Pyke giving the away side something to fight for. </p>

<p>More to follow.. </p>

<p>Ashley Fletcher (second left) scored a brace to help Middlesbrough advance to the next round</p>

<p>Shrewsbury put on a resilient performance to take the fight to their Championship opposition</p>

<p>Marcus Tavernier scored Middlesbrough's fourth goal to give them a two-goal advantage</p>

<p>Rekeil Pyke scored a third goal for Shrewsbury but they couldn't find the net a fourth time </p>

<p>The League One side gave Neil Warnock's Middlesbrough side a nervy night despite their loss</p>

<p>Shrewsbury's Shaun Walley and Middlesbrough's Djed Spence battle for possession </p>
